      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Most Playable 9-Letter Bingos</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">High base scores matter, but playability is equally important. These words use common tile distributions and connect easily to board letters.</p>

      <!-- Pill badges -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">ORGANIZED</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">19pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TERRORIZE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">18pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">MODERNIZE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">21pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">GALVANIZE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">22pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">OSTRACIZE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">20pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">BRUTALIZE</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">20pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <!-- Purple strategy tiles -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> Words ending in -IZE are your best source of 9-letter bingos. Add RE-, UN-, or suffixes like -ED/-RS to create 9+ letter plays through existing board tiles.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> Look for an existing E or D on the board. These are the most common hook letters for extending 7 rack tiles into a 9-letter play.</p></div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Landing 9-Letter Bingos</h2>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Playing a 9-letter bingo requires two conditions: the right tiles on your rack and the right letters already on the board positioned correctly.</p>

      <!-- Insight callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Nine-letter bingos through two existing tiles score an average of <span class="text-white font-medium">15-20% more</span> than standard 7-letter bingos because the longer word touches more premium squares across the board.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Purple strategy tiles -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Board Reading:</span> Scan for adjacent letter pairs that could be interior to a longer word. An R-E pair, T-I pair, or A-T pair on the board opens up dozens of 9-letter possibilities.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Rack Management:</span> If you have 6 strong bingo tiles plus one awkward letter, consider holding for a 9-letter play through the board rather than forcing a weaker 7-letter word.</p></div>
